<P>
   The ground around the garage is landscaped with oleanders and
rosemary. The herb's heavy scent lingers on the fingers of those
who touch it as they walk by. In the Middle Ages, it was a symbol
of remembrance and fidelity. Sprigs of it were dipped in gold and
given as keepsakes to honored wedding guests.
</P>
<P>
   The man on the roof landed among the rosemary.
</P>
<P>
   He had gone unnoticed on the streets of the city, as do all
those like him. He had been invisible on the roof of the garage. It
took only a few seconds for him to fall, hard and quiet, coming to
rest where he could no longer be ignored.
</P>
<P>
   Security found him on the ground near the garage's entrance, an
unknown man, silent, still, surrounded by the strong scent of
remembrance. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
