Carolina has upended the straight-talk express, and inside his
famously chatty bus, the afterglow of New Hampshire is dimming by
the day. Despite friendly crowds from Traverse City to Grand Rapids
to here in Saginaw _ and polls that show the Republican rivals neck
and neck in Michigan _ McCain and his aides say they are still
struggling to grasp what went awry in South Carolina. By Richard L.
Berke.
