about whether cellular telephone customers must continue to pay to
receive calls as well as to make them. Cellular companies, hoping
to make the cell phone a viable, everyday alternative to the desk
phone, have pressed for a rule change that would extend the
``calling party pays'' model of traditional telephone billing to
wireless calls. By Seth Schiesel.
