   RAIL-MERGER (Montreal) _ The president of Canadian National
Railway Co., Paul M. Tellier, wants to merge the Montreal-based CN
with a giant American railroad, Burlington Northern Santa Fe Corp.,
and create the most titanic railroad this continent has ever seen.
The behemoth would have 50,000 miles of track, freight service to
32 states and eight Canadian provinces, and cross-border access
from Halifax, Nova Scotia, to Mexico City to Long Beach, Calif. But
not everyone is willing to accept the vision of the new railroad or
the changes it represents. By Anthony DePalma.
