   HOLLYWOOD TURNS TO SPACE: Forget the United States and Russia.
The space race is between Disney and Warner Bros. More than three
decades after the Cold War contest to put the first man on the
moon, the rival studios are battling to land the first of two big
Mars movies in theaters. And those are just two of the
space-related movies coming out in 2000, beginning with ``Pitch
Black,'' a sci-fi horror movie about nasty nocturnal aliens.
