That's why one of my favorite drinking buddies is Al Hirschfeld.
The 96-year-old artist can't be bothered with sermons on grassy
undertones. He's a bourbon man. And when we go out together, he
prefers to keep drinking it past cocktails and through the meal,
which, by the way, he prefers to be steak. I love a guy who breaks
the rules, almost as much as I love breaking them myself. Because
my dirty little secret is: I'm drinking bourbon right along with
him. By Alex Witchel.
