A4737 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX     02-22 0447
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOR SPORTY TURF, START WITH TIF419 SOD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Where can I get Bermuda 419 grass seed? It's the grass used
in the Cotton Bowl in Dallas and The Ballpark in Arlington.
</P>
<P>
   _ M.G., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Tifton 419 Bermuda grass, also called Tif419, is not
available as a seed. ``It is vegetatively planted only'' _ meaning
sod, sprigged or plugged with live growing plants, according to
Jason Gray, turfgrass extension assistant with Texas A&AMP;M
University. ``No seeded varieties available will look anything like
Tif419.''
</P>
<P>
   You can special-order Tif419 sod from Thomas Brothers Grass at
4020 S. Cooper St. in Arlington. It sells for $131.67 per pallet
plus a $5 pallet deposit. For more information, call (817) 467-1103
or visit the Web site www.thomasbros.com.
</P>
<P>
   More information on Texas grasses is available from the Texas
Turfgrass Association's Web site, www.texasturf.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What's the name of the ``Law &AMP; Order'' theme song, and is it
available on CD?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.H., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: The unnamed theme is included on the 1994 CD ``Inventions
From the Blue Line'' by Mike Post, the composer of numerous
cop-show theme songs.
</P>
<P>
   ``Inventions'' also includes the themes from ``NYPD Blue,''
``Silk Stalkings,'' ``Renegade'' and ``Cop Files'' along with five
other songs used on ``Blue.''
</P>
<P>
   Post, a five-time Grammy winner, has written themes and music
for more than two dozen TV shows. His other themes include ``Hill
Street Blues,'' ``The Commish,'' ``Quantum Leap'' and ``The
Greatest American Hero.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Inventions'' is available from several retailers and directly
from the record label American Gramaphone Records for $9.98 plus
$4.50 shipping and handling. Call (800) 446-6860 for ordering
information.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I'm trying to find the name of a movie that starred Thelma
Ritter as a mother trying to find husbands for her three daughters.
Can you help?
</P>
<P>
   _ D.M.G., S. Grafton, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A: That's the 1963 comedy ``For Love or Money,'' which also
starred Kirk Douglas, Julie Newmar and William Bendix.
</P>
<P>
   The movie is out of print and did not turn up in a search.
CloseOutVideo.com, a Florida dealer specializing in hard-to-find
videos, has sold it but recently ran out of copies. To contact the
company, call (727) 447-4147 or visit the Web site
www.closeoutvideo.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
