<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    TALL TALES and SHORT STORIES: Rabble over Rebel flag
 &HT;    By Joe Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   LUFKIN, Texas _ In a recent column, I suggested that
African-Americans appropriate the Confederate flag, further
decorate it with a huge black circle that has a slash through it
and then fly it from a separate but equally prominent flag staff
over the Capitol of South Carolina.
</P>
<P>
   That way, white Southerners who revere the Rebel flag would have
some idea of the outrage blacks feel when seeing it flown in public
places.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail reaction was forthcoming. Here's a sampling:
</P>
<P>
   First this, from sirgregory5(at)juno.com:
</P>
<P>
   ``Can it be that I am the only person in the world who has ever
read a history book?
</P>
<P>
   ``Your article only shows you've jumped on the latest bandwagon,
and like all these other protesters, didn't check your facts.
</P>
<P>
   ``I am a staunch liberal Democrat. I'm not a redneck. I simply
speak the truth, and the truth is the Rebel flag is the last _ one
of many _ flags that stood for slavery.
</P>
<P>
   ``The U.S. flag, good Old Glory, besides standing for the
annihilation of Native Americans, the slaughter of Korean civilians
and the complete rip-off of Mexico, also stood for slavery for 100
years before there even was a Confederacy. Protest that.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Rebel flag flew for three years during the Civil War. The
U.S. 'slave' flag, along with others that waved over slave
auctions, flew for hundreds of years.
</P>
<P>
   ``The whole Rebel flag thing is an ignorant knee-jerk reaction
by a few unread, ignorant people who need something new to protest
about.
</P>
<P>
   ``The standard rebuttal is that the Rebel flag to blacks is like
the Nazi flag to Jews. It is not at all.
</P>
<P>
   ``The swastika is pure evil and there has never been or will
ever be anything that compares to it. It did not stand for one
single good thing.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Rebel battle flag is an easy scapegoat for ignorant people
who are too lazy to bother reading what really happened _ either
that, or they choose to ignore the straight truth.
</P>
<P>
   ``When it comes to slavery, the Rebel flag ain't nuthin'
compared to that Yankee flag.''
</P>
<P>
   Next this, from SOUTHB(at)aol.com:
</P>
<P>
   ``I can't figure out if you're on drugs or just stupid.
</P>
<P>
   ``During the Civil War, we defeated the forces of fascism that
tried to destroy our young country.
</P>
<P>
   ``We spent thousands of men's lives to stamp out that kind of
tyranny. As for the heritage of the Old South, screw the Old South
and every southern moron who revels in it.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Old South should be spending centuries trying to get back
in the good graces of the intelligent and principled republic.
</P>
<P>
   ``White southerners should be our permanent sub-class, picking
fruit, living in shacks and pondering their colossal ignorance.
</P>
<P>
   ``Anyone displaying a southern flag should be seen for the
lunatic he or she is and ostracized by the good people of this
country.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have never met a white southerner with the intelligence of a
turnip.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hurricanes, floods and twisters are just God's way of trying
to pull the handle and finally flush this scum-sucking part of the
country.''
</P>
<P>
   And finally this, from sotagal(AT)txucom.net:
</P>
<P>
   ``Thank you for your article on the Confederate flag. I couldn't
have said it better. If even one person's opinion is swayed, your
good deed for the year is covered!''
</P>
<P>
   Yes, isn't it pretty to think so.
</P>
<P>
   Joe Murray, editor-publisher emeritus of the Lufkin (Texas)
Daily News, is senior writer for Cox Newspapers. E-mail address is
jmurray(at)txucom.net. Mailing address, P.O. Box 151108, Lufkin,
Texas, 75915.)
</P>
