<HEADLINE>
AMERICAN CLASSIC STICKS TO BASICS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: Marge Powers' Cook's Corner column) 
 
 
By MARGE POWERS 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Daily News reader Shirley Freitas of Canoga Park has been
seeking a recipe for tuna casserole with potato chips and cream of
mushroom soup. This is an old American classic that has been
printed many times in many newspapers and magazines during the last
50 years.
</P>
<P>
   Six Daily News readers sent in the same lengthy recipe, while
two readers shared similar shorter versions, which came from
Campbell's Soup.
</P>
<P>
   Sandy Williams' sent along a version that was shared in a 1983
Daily News Food section by Jan Stoll of North Hollywood. It uses
cream of celery soup.
</P>
<P>
   This hearty casserole will make a comforting meal during the
winter season.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
TUNA CASSEROLE &QL; 
(Shared by Sandy Williams, Winnetka; Helen King, Newhall) &QL; 
1 (10 3/4-ounce) can cream of celery soup OR cream of mushroom
soup &QL; 
1/2 cup milk &QL; 
1 (6 1/2- OR 7-ounce) can tuna, drained and flaked &QL; 
1 cup cooked green peas &QL; 
1 1/4 cups lightly crumbled potato chips
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, blend soup and milk. Stir in tuna, peas and 1 cup
potato chips. Turn into a 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle top with
remaining 1/4 cup potato chips.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 25 minutes. Makes 4 servings.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
TUNA CASSEROLE &QL; 
(Shared by Susanne Romo, Burbank; Mary Morgan, West Hills; Bea
Duron, Inglewood; Mary Wright, Glendale; L.A. Wilson, Glendale;
Margie Turner, Los Angeles) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
1 (10 3/4-ounce) can cream of mushroom soup &QL; 
3/4 cup milk &QL; 
1/2 cup mayonnaise &QL; 
2 (7-ounce) cans solid white tuna, packed in water, drained &QL; 
1 (10-ounce) package frozen peas, thawed &QL; 
6 stalks celery, thinly sliced (about 2 cups) &QL; 
2 hard-cooked eggs, halved lengthwise and sliced &QL; 
1/2 cup drained sliced ripe olives &QL; 
1/2 cup crushed potato chips &QL; 
2 tablespoons butter, melted &QL; 
1/3 cup shredded Cheddar cheese OR grated Parmesan cheese &QL; 
2 tablespoons chopped parsley
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, mix soup, milk and mayonnaise. Flake tuna into pieces
and fold into soup mixture along with peas, celery, eggs and
olives.
</P>
<P>
   Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole. Top with potato chips,
drizzle with butter and sprinkle with cheese.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 375-degree oven, 20 to 25 minutes, until top
is browned and bubbly. Garnish with parsley before serving. Makes 6
servings. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
