<HEADLINE>
KEY RATES 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the daily key rates from The New York Times.
</P>
<P>
   --------------------Tuesday----Previous Day---Year Ago
</P>
<P>
   PRIME RATE ---------- 8.75 ------ 8.75 ------- 7.75
</P>
<P>
   DISCOUNT RATE ------- 5.25 ------ 5.25 ------- 4.50
</P>
<P>
   FEDERAL FUNDS(x) ---- 5.81 ------ 5.70 ------- 5.09
</P>
<P>
   3-MO. TREAS. BILLS -- 5.64 ------ 5.56 ------- 4.44
</P>
<P>
   6-MO. TREAS. BILLS -- 5.76 ------ 5.73 ------- 4.47
</P>
<P>
   10-YR. TREAS. INF(xx) 4.26 ------ 4.27 ------- 3.80
</P>
<P>
   10-YR. TREAS. NOTES - 6.36 ------ 6.48 ------- 5.01
</P>
<P>
   30-YR. TREAS. BONDS - 6.08 ------ 6.15 ------- 5.34
</P>
