<P>
   RAMPART-REBUFF (Los Angeles) _ A sharply divided Los Angeles
City Council rebuffed a proposal to create a new independent panel
to look at the Rampart Division scandal on Tuesday, saying it
wanted to wait to see what is developed by the LAPD and what steps
are taken by the Police Commission. The 8-6 vote against the
proposal from Councilman Joel Wachs, however, did not kill it
outright. Instead it was sent to the council's Public Safety
Committee - on which Wachs serves - for review at a later time with
no deadline set. By Rick Orlov. (Will run on the ``a'' national and
``n'' state news files.)
</P>
