<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Sweet replay for Holyfield
 &HT;    By Richard L. Eldredge
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Former heavyweight champion Evander Holyfield gets his ear
gnawed on again, this time in the new Sports Illustrated swimsuit
edition that hits newsstands today. His new assailant, however, is
far more attractive than Mike Tyson.
</P>
<P>
   In one photograph, the ex-champ is shown sparring with
supermodel Heidi Klum, and in another shot Klum re-enacts a scene
from the infamous Tyson bout by clamping her teeth on Holyfield's
earlobe.
</P>
<P>
   ``It caught me by surprise when Heidi bit my ear,'' Holyfield
says, ``but I didn't mind when I remembered that the last time
someone did that, I got $35 million.''
</P>
<P>
   In addition to Holyfield and the usual bevy of bathing beauties
such as cover model Daniela Pestova, Sports Illustrated ($5.99)
includes photos of Ben Crenshaw, Jason Kidd and other famous
athletes with their spouses, most of them in swimsuits.
</P>
<P>
   And, if some of the photos appear a little out of focus, don't
panic. There's nothing wrong with your eyes. You just need to slip
on the special 3-D glasses that are included for perusing the
magazine's first-ever three-dimensional section.
</P>
<P>
   The cardboard-and-plastic specs also can be worn to watch the
``Sports Illustrated Swimsuit 2000'' special airing at 8 p.m.
Saturday on TNT.
</P>
<P>
   Richard L. Eldredge writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
