<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES EDITOR'S NOTE FOR WEDNESDAY, FEBRUARY 23
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: This editor's note will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-BRADLEY-INQUIRY-NYT (moved on Sunday, Feb. 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Feb. 20,
about an interview with former Senator Bill Bradley on the ABC News
program ``This Week'' said Bradley had endorsed the appointment of
a special prosecutor to investigate campaign finance irregularities
by the Clinton-Gore campaign in 1996. While the article cited
Bradley's position correctly, the headline overstated it, saying,
``Bradley Calls for Inquiry Into '96 Fund-Raising.''
</P>
<P>
   Bradley was asked, ``Given the campaign finance problem and the
scandals of 1996, should we get to the bottom of what happened in
both parties, in particular the Democratic Party, by appointing a
special prosecutor to look into that?''
</P>
<P>
   Bradley replied: ``Yes, I think that it would be very important
to get to the bottom of it. I think a special prosecutor's one way
to do that.''  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
