<SLUG> BC-THQFOLO-GAME-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THQ EARNINGS POISED TO DECREASE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY JASON Z. COHEN  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   CALABASAS _ Look for a strong fourth quarter, followed by a dip
in the performance of video game maker THQ Inc. in the first half
of 2000, industry watchers said. Several factors are converging to
create the likelihood of a decrease in earnings this year, analysts
said.
</P>
<P>
   The company is expected to beat the First Call/Thompson
Financial consensus of 66 cents per share when it reports its 1999
fourth quarter results Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Edward Williams, stock analyst with Gerard Klauer Mattison &AMP;
Co., said the company is typically tight-lipped on financial
matters, but it released an estimate in January that said it would
exceed that estimate.
</P>
<P>
   Investors polled by WhisperNumber.com predict a much stronger
fourth quarter with an average estimate of 77 cents per share.
Williams said he has little faith in whisper numbers.
</P>
<P>
   THQ, along with the rest of the video game industry, is in a
technology shift. Consumers are slowing down their purchases of
games on existing systems in anticipation of the release of two new
game systems - Sega's Dreamcast and Sony's PlayStation 2.
</P>
<P>
   THQ is developing games for both systems, he said.
</P>
<P>
   ``They'll have their first game out for Dreamcast in the June
quarter, but they won't get meaningful revenues until the fall,''
Williams said. ``One of the key things to understand about the
industry is that the June quarter in particular tends to be a light
quarter.''
</P>
<P>
   But last year, THQ had strong sales in the first and second
quarters, releasing games under its license with World Championship
Wrestling en masse before the license expired.
</P>
<P>
   ``They had very large shipments in the first half of fiscal 1999
and relatively light shipments in the second half of fiscal 1999,''
Williams said.
</P>
<P>
   In comparison with last year's strong first and second quarters,
this year's first half will appear weak, Williams said.
</P>
<P>
   ``The key thing with all video game companies is they really
can't be run on a quarter-by-quarter basis,'' he said. ``For 20
consecutive quarters, they will have reported positive
year-over-year earnings. That streak comes to an end.''
</P>
<P>
   The company's stock has slid to roughly half of its November
value, largely on investor concerns about THQ's future performance.
Shares of THQ closed at $17.625 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The company faces two shareholder lawsuits alleging selective
disclosure of financial information involving suspected leaks of
the company's projections for its first- and second-quarter
performances.
</P>
<P>
   Lawsuits were filed by San Diego-based Milberg Weiss Bershad
Haynes &AMP; Lerach and Philadelphia-based Spector, Roseman and
Kodroff. Principals of both firms were unavailable for comment
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   THQ spokeswoman Liz Bell said the company has not been served
with copies of either lawsuit, and it typically does not comment on
litigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
