<HEADLINE>
SPORTSMANSHIP? NAH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC coach Henry Bibby could be setting off another
controversy this week, as he intends to prevent the Trojans from
shaking hands with Oregon State players following Thursday's game
at the Sports Arena.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't want to get cheap-shotted,'' Bibby said, referring to
last week's postgame brawl between USC and Arizona State that
resulted in Trojans guard Jeff Trepagnier and Sun Devils forwards
Awvee Storey and Tanner Shell being put on probation by the
Pacific-10 Conference.
</P>
<P>
   Asked if he was firmly committed to keeping the Trojans from
taking part in any posgame handshakes, Bibby said, ``Absolutely.''
</P>
<P>
   Bibby said he was also considering not letting his staff shake
hands with the Oregon State coaches during the traditional postgame
show of sportsmanship.
</P>
<P>
   ``I haven't decided that yet,'' Bibby said. ``More than likely
(we won't).''
</P>
<P>
   Bibby's anger over the Arizona State incident had not subsided
Tuesday and he spoke again at length over his displeasure with Sun
Devils coach Rob Evans.
</P>
<P>
   Evans said Saturday that USC wrote lewd comments about ASU on
the practice basketballs and he claimed the Trojans' Friday
practice spilled over into the Sun Devils' practice time, in an
attempt to distract ASU before the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're liars,'' Bibby said. ``Rob Evans lied and tried to
frame me and my basketball team. A good man would have come and
talked to me. But he didn't come to me.''
</P>
<P>
   Bibby said it was too late for him and Evans to settle their
differences amicably.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't have anything to say,'' Bibby said. ``If he wanted to
talk, talk before the game. That's what a class act would do, not
try to plant something. We were framed. I'll take a lie detector
test and put up $10,000 right now.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have been portrayed as the bad guys and that's not fair. It
was a setup. They framed us. It was a great old ploy because they
needed a win. It was very unlawful for them to make those
accusations.''
</P>
<P>
   Evans was asked Tuesday if there was lingering resentment over
the altercation. ``From whom? I don't know on their side. People
who were involved know what happened. I don't have any hard
feelings.''
</P>
<P>
   Even though the Pac-10 settled the matter, Bibby said he has
sent the conference a report of 21 incidents during the game that
showed Arizona State committing dangerous fouls.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not asking for a replay of the basketball game, we're
asking for fairness,'' Bibby said. ``Something has to be done.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Clancy has X-rays: Forward Sam Clancy underwent a second set
of X-rays Tuesday morning which showed his broken right foot was
healing as scheduled. Clancy began light running for the first time
during Tuesday's practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``My foot looks a lot better on the X-ray this time,'' Clancy
said. ``I still think I'll be back for the Cal game (March 3).''
</P>
<P>
   __ Traffic advisory: Fans attending Thursday's game at the
Sports Arena should be aware that a soccer match between Canada and
Trinidad and Tobago is scheduled at the Coliseum at 8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   __ Elmore honored: Guard Tiffany Elmore has been named the
Pac-10 women's basketball player of the week after leading the
Women of Troy to a sweep of the Arizona schools. She is the firsplayer honored with the award since Tina Thompson in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   USC (11-11, 6-6) has won three games in a row for the first time
since the 1996-97 season.
</P>
</TEXT>
